00:29:18.059 --> 00:29:19.610
far.

00:29:19.610 --> 00:29:25.190
If you even go back to
Victorian times, a Victorian detective like

00:29:25.190 --> 00:29:28.659
Sherlock Holmes would have thought, for example,
if somebody,

00:29:28.659 --> 00:29:34.809
if a murder had been committed in London,
and the accused could prove he was in New

00:29:34.809 --> 00:29:38.929
York the same day,
then he couldn't have done the murder.

00:29:38.929 --> 00:29:43.600
Because in Victorian times it was literally
impossible to be in London and New York

00:29:43.600 --> 00:29:44.600
on the same day.

00:29:44.600 --> 00:29:46.929
Now, of course, it's commonplace.

00:29:46.929 --> 00:29:53.100
The eminent science fiction writer, Arthur
C. Clarke, summed the point up as Clarke's

00:29:53.100 --> 00:29:54.759
third law.

00:29:54.759 --> 00:30:01.509
Any sufficiently advanced
technology is indistinguishable from magic.

00:30:01.509 --> 00:30:06.669
The more you think about it, the more you
realize the very idea of the supernatural

00:30:06.669 --> 00:30:09.249
miracle is nonsense.

00:30:09.249 --> 00:30:14.570
If something happened that appears to be inexplicable
by science, you can safely conclude one of

00:30:14.570 --> 00:30:16.110
two things.

00:30:16.110 --> 00:30:22.220
Either it really didn't happen, the observer
was mistaken or was lying or was tricked,

00:30:22.220 --> 00:30:27.249
or we've exposed a shortcoming in
present day science.

00:30:27.249 --> 00:30:32.539
If present day science encounters an observation
or experimental result that it cannot explain,

00:30:32.539 --> 00:30:36.379
then we
should not rest until we've proved our science

00:30:36.379 --> 00:30:39.769
so that it can provide an explanation.

00:30:39.769 --> 00:30:45.700
If it requires a radically new kind of
science, a revolutionary science so strange

00:30:45.700 --> 00:30:51.889
that it, sorry, so strange that old scientists
scarcely recognize it as science

00:30:51.889 --> 00:30:54.070
at all, that's fine too.

00:30:54.070 --> 00:30:55.639
It's happened before.

00:30:55.639 --> 00:31:02.489
But don't ever be lazy enough, defeatists
enough, cowardly enough, to say

00:31:02.489 --> 00:31:05.259
it must be supernatural because I don't understand
it.

00:31:05.259 --> 00:31:07.970
Or it must be a miracle.

00:31:07.970 --> 00:31:12.549
Say instead that it's a puzzle,
it's strange, it's a challenge that we should

00:31:12.549 --> 00:31:14.220
rise to.

00:31:14.220 --> 00:31:17.210
Whether we rise to the challenge by questioning
the truth of the

00:31:17.210 --> 00:31:24.809
observation, or by expanding our science in
new and exciting directions, the proper and

00:31:24.809 --> 00:31:30.879
brave response to any such challenge
is to tackle it head on.

00:31:30.879 --> 00:31:35.700
And until we've found a proper answer to the
mystery, it's perfectly OK to simply say,

00:31:35.700 --> 00:31:40.539
this is something we don't yet understand
but we're working on it.

00:31:40.539 --> 00:31:43.159
It's the only honest thing to do.

